name: Gov. Kim Reynolds
tweet: Let’s seize this opportunity and make the next decade Iowa’s best.

name: Gov. Kim Reynolds
tweet: So as we move into the next decade, let’s put Iowans first. Let’s be bold and visionary.

name: Gov. Kim Reynolds
tweet: As we head into this legislative session, let’s not focus solely on the next 12 months. This is a time to chart the path for the next ten years. #OpportunityLivesHere

name: Gov. Kim Reynolds
tweet: #OpportunityLivesHere because of the ingenuity of our people. If IA is going to thrive in the next decade, we must make sure that government isn’t stifling that ingenuity. It's been far too long since we’ve modernized our licensing structure. That’s what I’m calling for today.

name: Gov. Kim Reynolds
tweet: Together, we can help put returning citizens on a path to redemption. We can help them become productive members of society, reduce recidivism, and make our communities a safer place.

name: Gov. Kim Reynolds
tweet: You can’t imagine the gratitude and dignity that Iowans feel when they’re told they can once again exercise what Ronald Reagan called “the crown jewel of American liberties.”

name: Gov. Kim Reynolds
tweet: I am renewing my support to amend our Constitution so that it no longer bars felons from voting after they’ve served their sentence. #OpportunityLivesHere

name: Gov. Kim Reynolds
tweet: But it’s more than that. When someone has lost their way, we’re called to seek them out—to leave the 99 to find the one. I believe in that calling...

name: Gov. Kim Reynolds
tweet: Those in our correctional facilities are serving time for a reason, but when they leave, we want them to succeed.

name: Gov. Kim Reynolds
tweet: I’ve made it a priority of this administration to focus on prisoner re-entry and rehabilitation, because our prisons shouldn’t be one stop in a circle that leads back to prison. #OpportunityLivesHere

name: Gov. Kim Reynolds
tweet: Childcare is the next workforce issue we need to tackle. It’s another barrier for families looking for a way up. For some, it’s about affordability; for others, access is the issue; and for thousands of Iowans, it’s both. This year we need to act. #OpportunityLivesHere

name: Gov. Kim Reynolds
tweet: @FutureReadyIowa will infuse Iowa’s workforce with thousands of skilled employees, providing much needed support to our growing businesses.

name: Gov. Kim Reynolds
tweet: Over 6,000 Iowans are already receiving the Last Dollar Scholarship, almost 80 percent of which are adult learners. That’s 6,000 Iowans who are on their way to a rewarding career.

name: Gov. Kim Reynolds
tweet: Iowans who are looking for a way up are finding that opportunity.

name: Gov. Kim Reynolds
tweet: When it comes to workforce opportunities, Iowa is in a strong position. We have thousands of open jobs in rewarding careers. That’s why we launched @FutureReadyIowa. #OpportunityLivesHere

name: Gov. Kim Reynolds
tweet: The budget I’m presenting to you today makes another historic investment, with over $103 million in new funding so that Iowa schools can maintain the best teachers and classrooms in the world.

name: Gov. Kim Reynolds
tweet: In 2019, we made historic investments in K-12 education, with over $90 million in new money, including an increase in per-pupil funding and transportation equity. #OpportunityLivesHere

name: Gov. Kim Reynolds
tweet: In the last year alone, we’ve expanded high-school registered apprenticeships and launched the work-based learning clearinghouse, and this year will be adding $1 million for work-based learning coordinators to be covered by operational-sharing agreements.

name: Gov. Kim Reynolds
tweet: One of the best ways for students to learn is through hands-on experience, which is why we’re making Iowa a leader in work-based learning.

name: Gov. Kim Reynolds
tweet: I’m calling on the Legislature to take computer science statewide and ensure every student, at every level, has access to this new basic skill.

name: Gov. Kim Reynolds
tweet: If there’s something Iowans have always understood, it’s that there is no better path to opportunity than a quality education. #OpportunityLivesHere

name: Gov. Kim Reynolds
tweet: Today, I’m requesting that we appropriate an additional $15 million and adjust our state match so we can continue to leverage private and federal funding to build out broadband to every part of Iowa. #OpportunityLivesHere

name: Gov. Kim Reynolds
tweet: I’ve also directed DHS to remove barriers that are restricting schools from partnering with telehealth providers... What used to be a 70-mile drive in the middle of the school day can now be a walk down the hall.

name: Gov. Kim Reynolds
tweet: That’s why I’m taking steps to increase the number of doctors who are willing and able to provide OB services in all four corners of our state.

name: Gov. Kim Reynolds
tweet: We must also do more to promote and support maternal health. Fewer doctors and fewer hospitals are delivering babies and providing care for mothers, especially outside our urban areas.

name: Gov. Kim Reynolds
tweet: And when I say all stages of life, I mean to include the unborn. We must protect life by making clear, through an amendment, that our constitution does not grant a right to abortion.

name: Gov. Kim Reynolds
tweet: As we move into 2020, I’m focused on the overall wellness of all Iowans, in every part of the State, in all stages of life.  #OpportunityLivesHere

name: Gov. Kim Reynolds
tweet: If we take this bold step, right now, then whoever is standing at this podium in 10, 20, or 30 years—Republican or Democrat—can proudly say what I can say today: The condition of our State is strong.

name: Gov. Kim Reynolds
tweet: The #InvestinIowaAct will bring meaningful change to Iowans in the very first year. But most important, it looks to the future. To our children and theirs.

name: Gov. Kim Reynolds
tweet: I’m also proposing, through the #InvestinIowaAct, that we reduce property tax levies and provide the needed mental health funding through the State general fund.

name: Gov. Kim Reynolds
tweet: I’m proposing to cut income taxes by an additional 10% for almost every Iowan, with lower-income Iowans receiving as much as a 25% cut next year.

name: Gov. Kim Reynolds
tweet: I have no interest in raising taxes, so any increase in revenue from a sales tax must be more than offset by additional tax cuts. That starts with continuing to reduce our uncompetitive income-tax rates.

name: Gov. Kim Reynolds
tweet: These changes will make our vision a reality. It’s an investment in our future. And it’s an investment in those who are our future.

name: Gov. Kim Reynolds
tweet: I will introduce the Invest in Iowa Act, a bill that will. significantly cut income taxes, create a sustainable funding source for our mental health system, reduce the burden of property taxpayers, and fund the Natural Resources and Outdoor Recreation Trust. #OpportunityLivesHere

name: Gov. Kim Reynolds
tweet: That kind of planning takes a bold vision. A vision that preserves our heritage while seizing opportunities.

name: Gov. Kim Reynolds
tweet: That’s why this year, 2020, we need to plan for 2030 and 2040. We need to seize the opportunities that exist so that years from now, the next generation of Iowans will inherit an Iowa whose greatness comes as no surprise to anyone.

name: Gov. Kim Reynolds
tweet: But we cannot take anything for granted. We cannot become complacent...

name: Gov. Kim Reynolds
tweet: Our unemployment rate has gone from a near-record high to a record low. Instead of cutting school budgets, we’re cutting taxes. Our cash reserves are full, wages are going up, and Iowans once again believe we’re headed in the right direction.
